body:


<div class="container mt-5">
<h2>Talks</h2>

<ul>
<li>Building a 'boring' data platform, TPXImpact, July 2023.
<li>Transport Data Commons, Oxford University, 2022.
<li>Artificial Intelligence: The Revolution for SMEs, University of Chichester, 2019.
<li>Tracking Property Changes: a talk on maintaining property data in city centres. Future High Streets Forum, Nottingham, 2019.
<li>Data: Past, present &amp; future for city centres, British BIDs, Cambridge University, 2017.
<li>Public Policy Exchange: The Future of the High Street, London, 2017.
<li>Revive &amp; Thrive: Monitoring Town Centre Data, Tamworth, 2015.
<li>Big Data - should we be scared? University of Chichester, 2015.
</ul>

<h2>Media</h2>
<ul>
<li>BBC South Today <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CsC0ExLgeCc">Footfall in Chichester High Street</a>, 2016.</li>
<li>BBC Radio Solent, Live Interview on Chichester's Footfall, 2016.</li>
<li>Newham Recorder, on the creation of a Business Improvement District, 2014.</li>
<li>Somewhen 2003-2005... a website I created featured on CNN, BBC, Harvard Uni.</li>
<li>Computer Shopper Magazine, Blogwise run by Sven Latham, 2006 (UK).</li>
</ul>
<p>Also did a piece for a radio station in Quebec (I think), three mentions in Radio 2 Website of the Day, Portsmouth News multiple times,
Chichester Observer a few times, and somehow broke the news that Yahoo was working on blogs, which got on the 
<a href="https://news.slashdot.org/story/03/08/25/122226/yahoo-experimenting-with-blogs">front page of Slashdot</a> once and
<a href="https://www.infoworld.com/article/2645805/yahoo-blogs-.html">picked up elsewhere</a> (2003).</p>

